{% comment %}
  Paws & Co. Homepage — Git-controlled layout
  ───────────────────────────────────────────
  Using a .liquid template (not .json) so GitHub pushes actually overwrite this file.
  Shopify treats templates/*.json as merchant-owned; templates/*.liquid as code.

  Each {% section %} tag renders a section with its schema-defined settings + blocks.
  Merchants CAN still customize each section's content via the theme editor — they
  just can't add/remove/reorder sections on the homepage from the editor.
  The layout order is controlled from this file in Git.
{% endcomment %}

